---
import SAGPLayout from "../../layouts/SAGPLayout.astro";
---

<SAGPLayout title="Events | Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy">

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="kicker">Events</div>
    <h1>Scholarly conversation across years, continents, and traditions.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      SAGP events bring scholars together to present research, test developing
      ideas, honor distinguished work, and continue a conversation that began
      more than seventy years ago.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>The rhythm of the Society</h2>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Annual Conference</h3>
      <p>
        The Society’s annual conference gathers scholars for moderated sessions
        devoted to original research in Ancient Greek philosophy.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/events/annual-conference/">Learn about the Annual Conference</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Distinguished Lectureship</h3>
      <p>
        Each year, SAGP honors a scholar whose work has made very substantial
        contributions to the field.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/events/distinguished-lectureship/">Explore the Lectureship</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Works in Progress</h3>
      <p>
        The Works in Progress series gives scholars, especially early-career and
        mid-career scholars, a setting for presenting developing work and
        receiving constructive feedback.
      </p>
      <p><a href="/events/works-in-progress/">View the series</a></p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Conversation, not simply presentation</h2>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
      SAGP events are designed around intellectual exchange. Annual conference
      sessions bring multiple scholars into conversation around shared themes.
      Distinguished Lectures include commentary and discussion. Works in
      Progress sessions invite feedback while research is still developing.
    </p>
    <p>
      Across these formats, the Society expresses one of its central commitments:
      scholarship flourishes through careful argument, generous criticism, and
      sustained dialogue.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>International by design</h2>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
      Many SAGP events are held online or made accessible to scholars across
      time zones. This reflects the Society’s outward-looking character and its
      commitment to supporting a global community of scholars in Ancient Greek
      philosophy.
    </p>
    <div class="callout">
      The Society’s events are not isolated announcements. They are recurring
      expressions of its scholarly life.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</SAGPLayout>
